From: Armbian
Subject: bananapi-m2-ultra: disable DE2 in u-boot for HDMI EDID detection

Carried over from the v2024.01-era board patch, rebased onto v2026.07-rc4's
Bananapi_M2_Ultra_defconfig. Disabling the DE2 display driver in u-boot improves
HDMI EDID detection on R40 (https://forum.armbian.com/topic/13651). R40 has a DE2
engine, so the option is valid here.

--- a/configs/Bananapi_M2_Ultra_defconfig
+++ b/configs/Bananapi_M2_Ultra_defconfig
@@ -23,3 +23,4 @@
 CONFIG_SCSI=y
 CONFIG_USB_EHCI_HCD=y
 CONFIG_USB_OHCI_HCD=y
+CONFIG_VIDEO_DE2=n
